name: boolean
definition: A binary data type that represents two possible values- true or false

name: double
definition: A 64-bit number expressed in the decimal-point notation with an optional + or - prefix and an optional exponent after a trailing e

name: double array
definition: An array in which each 64 bits represents a field of the double data type

name: enumeration
definition: A set of named values (elements) indexed by an integer

name: float
definition: A 32-bit number expressed in the decimal-point notation with an optional + or - prefix and an optional exponent after a trailing e

name: float array
definition: An array in which each 32 bits represents a field of the float data type

name: geophysicalCoordinate
definition: A point on the surface of the earth identified by its latitude, longitude, and optionally altitude

name: int16
definition: 16-bit signed integer for range -32768 to 32767

name: int32
definition: 32-bit signed integer for values -2147483648 to 2147483647

name: int8
definition: 8-bit signed integer for range -128 to 127

name: int8 array
definition: An array in which each 64 bits represents a field of the int8 data type

name: string
definition: A sequence of characters treated as text

name: string array
definition: An array of strings delimited with a comma

name: uint16
definition: 16-bit unsigned integer for range 0 to 65535

name: uint16 array
definition: An array in which each 64 bits represents a field of the uint16 data type

name: uint32
definition: 32-bit unsigned integer for range 0 to 4294967295

name: uint64
definition: 64-bit unsigned integer for range 0 to 18446744073709551615

name: uint8
definition: 8-bit unsigned integer for values 0 to 255

name: uint8 array
definition: An array in which each 64 bits represents a field of the uint8 data type
